      • onClickMainDeletePartBtn

        public void onClickMainDeletePartBtn​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        Delete Button to remove part from inventory and update the part table to show that it has been deleted. Confirmation pop up to make sure user wants to delete part, and error pop up if part cannot be deleted.

      • onClickMainDeleteProdBtn

        public void onClickMainDeleteProdBtn​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        Delete button removes product from inventory and updates the part table to show that it has been deleted. Confirmation pop up to make sure user wants to delete product, and error pop up if product cannot be deleted.

      • onClickMainModProdBtn

        public void onClickMainModProdBtn​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Modify button calls sendProd method to take the data of the selected product and send it to the Modify Product scene. Scene changes to Modify Product scene. Pop up error if no product is selected.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • onClickPartSearch

        public void onClickPartSearch​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        Takes partial name or partial id to search for the part in the Inventory.allParts List. An error pops up if part is not found. Table is refreshed to display what parts are around based off partial search. If search field is empty, the table displays all the parts in the Inventory.

      • onClickProdSearch

        public void onClickProdSearch​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        Takes partial name or partial id to search for the product in the Inventory.allProds List. An error pops up if product is not found. Table is refreshed to display what products are around based off partial search. If search field is empty, the table displays all the products in the Inventory.
